In their quest to gain automatic promotion to the Premier Soccer League (PSL), Black Leopards Football Club has appointed former Polokwane City Football Club Assistant Coach Sly Mosala as new assistant to their coach, Jean Francois Losciuto. According to a club official, Mosala was appointed last Friday and will be with the club until the end of the season. He is a good coach and we believe he will help us in the promotion campaign, the official said. Lidoda Duvha is currently in second position of the National First Division table with 39 points after 23 matches and nine points behind log leaders Thanda Royal Zulu. They hope to consolidate their position when they meet 9th placed Jomo Cosmos at Olen Park on 26 April. Story: Herbert Rachuene &gt;&gt;herbert@mailbox.co.za &nbsp;